  "title": "Insurance Agreement",
  "description": "An Agreement between an insurer and a customer to insure a risk object against some risk.\r\n\r\nAn insurance agreement is the core contract between an insurance company (the insurer) and a customer (the policyholder).\r\n\r\nIt is the section of an insurance policy that sets out the insurers promise:\r\n\r\nwhat risks or events are covered (e.g., death, accident, illness, loss of property),\r\nunder what conditions the insurer will pay, and\r\nwhat obligations the policyholder must meet (like paying premiums).",
